'''SMSS J215728.21-360215.1'''，通常稱為'''J2157-3602'''，是迄{{As of|lc=y|2018}}所知{{link-en|成長最快的黑洞| List of most massive black holes }}和[[類星體列表#極端|最強大的類星體]]。這個類星體的[[紅移|紅移]]z=4.75<ref name="Wolf"/>，對應於[[同移距離|同移距離]]為距離地球{{val|25e9|ul=ly}}和[[距離測量_(宇宙學)#距離的類型|光行距]]{{val|12.5e9|ul=ly}}。[[澳大利亞國立大學|澳大利亞國立大學]]在2018年5月宣布它是[[賽丁泉天文台|賽丁泉天文台]]的{{link-en|星圖家望遠鏡|SkyMapper}}發現的。它的內在[[光度|熱輻射光度]]是{{val|6.95e14|ul=Solar luminosity}}（{{val|2.66e41|ul=W}}）<ref name="Wolf">{{Cite journal|last=Wolf|first=Christian|last2=Bian|first2=Fuyan|last3=Onken|first3=Christopher|last4=Schmidt|first4=Brian|last5=Tisserand|first5=Patrick|last6=Alonzi|first6=Noura|last7=Hon|first7=Wei Jeat|last8=Tonry|first8=John|date=May 11, 2018|title=Discovery of the most ultra-luminous QSO using Gaia, SkyMapper and WISE|arxiv=1805.04317|journal=[[Publications_of_the_Astronomical_Society_of_Australia|Publications of the Astronomical Society of Australia]]|volume=35|pages=|bibcode=2018PASA...35...24W|doi=10.1017/pasa.2018.22}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/05/17/science/hungry-black-hole.html|title=A Very Hungry Black Hole Is Found, Gorging on Stars|last=Overbye|first=Dennis|date=May 17, 2018|work=The New York Times|access-date=May 25, 2018|archive-date=2021-05-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210505053540/https://www.nytimes.com/2018/05/17/science/hungry-black-hole.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.yahoo.com/news/newly-discovered-apos-monster-apos-164700567.html|title=Newly Discovered 'Monster' Black Hole Has a Terrifying Diet|last=Paoletta|first=Rae|date=May 15, 2018|work=Yahoo News|access-date=May 25, 2018|archive-date=2020-10-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201009111917/https://www.yahoo.com/news/newly-discovered-apos-monster-apos-164700567.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://thespacereporter.com/article.php?n=newly-discovered-black-hole-is-fastest-growing-on-record&id=147140|title=Newly discovered black hole is fastest growing on record|last=Scalise|first=Joseph|date=May 16, 2018|work=The Space Reporter|access-date=May 15, 2018|archive-date=2020-07-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200705014543/https://thespacereporter.com/article.php?n=newly-discovered-black-hole-is-fastest-growing-on-record&id=147140|dead-url=yes}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://interestingengineering.com/fastest-growing-black-hole-ever-has-been-discovered-by-astronomers|title=Fastest Growing Black Hole Ever Has Been Discovered by Astronomers|last=Papadopoulos|first=Loukia|date=May 21, 2018|work=Interesting Engineering|access-date=May 25, 2018|archive-date=2022-02-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220202161610/https://interestingengineering.com/fastest-growing-black-hole-ever-has-been-discovered-by-astronomers|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

